for anyone having viewing problems with vlc there are tweaks to enhance it such as Video tweaks like changing the video output to direct x and the volume from this website http://lifehacker.com/5920290/how-to-fix-movies-that-are-really-quiet-then-really-loud , and this one for the video quailty http://blog.thewombat.org/2008/11/how-to-use-vlc-096-as-upscaling-media.html , and it would pay to go into the effects and visuals and change the volume equilizer to classical and click 2 pass it will almost get rid of the background buzzing noise
